% CEEMDAN function implementation
function imf = ceemdan(x, ensembleSize, maxIterations)
    imf = zeros(ensembleSize, length(x));

    for k = 1:ensembleSize
        xEnsemble = x + randn(size(x));  % Add white noise to each ensemble

        h = xEnsemble;
        iter = 0;

        while iter < maxIterations && ~ismonotonic(h)
            d = h;
            iter = iter + 1;

            for j = 1:length(h)
                h(j) = mean(spline(t, d, t(j)) + d - h);
            end
        end

        imf(k, :) = h;
    end
end

% Helper function to check monotonicity
function monotonic = ismonotonic(x)
    monotonic = all(diff(x) >= 0) || all(diff(x) <= 0);
end
```

Please note that this implementation is a simplified version, and there may be more complex variations of CEEMDAN. Additionally, be aware that this implementation may not produce the same results as a specialized CEEMDAN algorithm.
